  <!-- ═══ RISKS ═══ -->
  <h2>Risks and Considerations</h2>
  <p>No valuation model is complete without addressing potential pitfalls.</p>

  <h3>Upside risks (our number could be too low)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Medical Device Supercycle:</strong> If devices like FreeStyle Libre or structural heart products significantly exceed adoption forecasts, 8% FCF growth could prove severely under-estimated.</li>
    <li><strong>Margin Expansion:</strong> Improved supply chain logistics and pricing leverage in newer med-tech innovations could drive margin expansions faster than historic norms.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Downside risks (our number could be too high)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Regulatory Pressures:</strong> Price controls, shifting reimbursement rates, or unforeseen FDA setbacks.</li>
    <li><strong>Nutrition Segment Weakness:</strong> Lasting brand damage or persistent competition issues in the pediatric nutrition market following recent historical recalls could suppress cash flow.</li>
  </ul>

